description:
RESPONSIBILITIES




 As an Application Support Engineer in a very rich and dynamic environment, you will work closely with the development team. You will be in charge of the functional and technical support of the production environments.




 What you will do:




 • Daily support tasks (90%):




 • Technical and functional support of the production;




 • Monitoring and request / Incident management;




 • Pick\\-up calls on a shared hotline;




 • Features explanations;




 • Knowledge transfer for new joiners and users;




 • Crisis management if needed;




 • Release management (5%):




 • Study release impacts on production;




 • Install applicative packages coming from development team on pre\\-pre\\-production environment;




 • Install new version in production and ensure post deployment checks;




 • Continuous improvement (5%):




 • Reach for a full automation of manual tasks, delivery process and monitoring




 • Advanced knowledge on Agile Testing




 • Drive Agile ceremonies Understanding of Iterative model/Testing methodologies of SDLC




 • Manage the communication between the users and the technical / functional team




 • Drive the incident management calls and make sure




 • Make available the knowledge of the local activity by promoting and updating specific documentation




 • Contribute to transformation topics and deliver continuous improvements




 • Identify improvement areas and lead the automation of manual checks/tasks




 • Propose transformation of existing processes both for the business or our production services activities




 • Should be a self starter, having passion for technology and must be a quick leaner.




 • Provide support to the junior team members




 • Participate in DR and BCP activities










**Profile** 




 REQUIRED PROFILE




 • Finance functional knowledge and technical background in SQL/Unix




 • At least 4\\-8 years experience in support;




 • Good knowledge in Unix, SQL, and finance;




 • Good command of English, both written and spoken. French would be a plus.




 • Good analytical skills and ability to summarize key messages.




 • Good communication skills, adaptability and self\\-control;




 • Client\\-driven approach \\& service oriented;




 • High autonomy and ability to work in a stressful environment, rigor, cooperation, and team spirit.
